1
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:23,079
Where are you? Come out!

2
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,248
Come out!

3
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:28,084
Come on out.

4
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:33,169
I'm coming to get you.

5
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:37,506
Where are you, you little rascal?
I'm coming to get you.

6
00:01:37,556 --> 00:01:39,512
Hm.

7
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:42,307
Where is my little birthday girl, hm?

8
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:46,474
I'm going to gobble her up
when I find her.

9
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:48,354
Oh!

10
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,356
I'm going to eat you. I am.

11
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:55,979
Och, Fergus, no weapons on the table.

12
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:58,240
Can I shoot an arrow?
Canl? Canl? Can 1? Can I?

13
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:00,534
Please? Can I?

14
00:02:00,621 --> 00:02:03,658
Not with that. Why not...

15
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,038
Use your very own?

16
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:08,413
Happy birthday, my wee darling!

17
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:14,381
Now, there's a good girl.

18
00:02:14,426 --> 00:02:17,008
Draw all the way back now
to your cheek. That's right.

19
00:02:18,305 --> 00:02:20,296
Keep both eyes open.

20
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:23,257
And, loose!

21
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:27,386
I missed.
Go and fetch it, then.

22
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:32,691
A bow, Fergus? She's a lady.

23
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:34,809
Ooh! You!

24
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:13,269
A will-o'-the-wisp.

25
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,692
They are real.

26
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:34,286
Elinor:
Merida, come along, sweetheart.

27
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,500
We're leaving now.
Merida: I saw a wisp.

28
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:40,626
I saw a wisp.
A wisp?

29
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:46,015
You know, some say that
will-o'-the-wisps lead you to your fate.

30
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:48,558
Oh, aye. Or an arrow.
Och!

31
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:51,637
Come on, let's be off before we see
a dancing Tatty Bogle.

32
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:54,144
Or a giant having a jigger
in the bluebells.

33
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,145
Your father doesn't believe in magic.

34
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,651
Well, he should. Because it's true.

35
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,364
Mor'du! Elinor, run!

36
00:04:03,452 --> 00:04:05,408
Sirel

37
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:15,167
Come on, you!

38
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,802
Merida: Some say our destiny
is tied to the land...

39
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:35,347
As much a part of us as we are of it.

40
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:42,529
Others say fate is woven together
like a cloth.

41
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:47,367
So that one's destiny intertwines
with many others.

42
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:56,373
It's the one thing we search for
or fight to change.

43
00:04:58,173 --> 00:05:00,164
Some never find it.

44
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:05,544
But there are some who are led.

45
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:13,301
The story of how my father lost his leg

46
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:15,917
to the demon bear Mor'du
became legend.

47
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,689
I became a sister fo three new brothers.

48
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:24,730
The princes.
Hamish, Hubert and Harris.

49
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,740
Wee devils, more like.

50
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:30,319
They get away with murder.

51
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,654
I can never get away with anything.

52
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:36,662
I'm the Princess.

53
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,368
Oh!

54
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:40,412
Merida: I'm the example.

55
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,425
I've got duties, responsibilities,
expectations.

56
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:47,298
My whole life is planned out,

57
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:49,345
preparing for the day I become...

58
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,842
Well, my mother.

59
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:53,767
She's in charge
of every single day of my life.

60
00:05:57,232 --> 00:06:00,724
Aye, Robin, jolly Robin,
and thou shalt know of mine.

61
00:06:00,777 --> 00:06:01,892
Project!

62
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,893
And thou shalt know of mine!

63
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:07,522
Enunciate. You must be understood
from anywhere in the room,

64
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:09,232
or it's all for naught.

65
00:06:09,286 --> 00:06:11,777
This is all for naught.
I heard that!

66
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,408
From the top.

67
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:16,414
A Princess must be knowledgeable
about her kingdom.

68
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:19,952
She does not doodle.

69
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:24,582
That's a c, dear.

70
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:33,390
A Princess does not chortle.

71
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,512
Mm!
Does not stuff her gob!

72
00:06:35,604 --> 00:06:37,310
Rises early.

73
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:39,183
Is compassionate...

74
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:40,684
Patient, cautious,

75
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:41,775
clean.

76
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:48,815
And above all, a Princess
strives for... well, perfection.

77
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:51,988
Merida: But every once in a while,

78
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:56,830
there's a day
when I don't have to be a Princess.

79
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:01,918
No lessons, no expectations.

80
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:04,337
A day where anything can happen.

81
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:08,918
A day I can change my fate.

82
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:10,218
Yah!

83
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:27,062
When cold wind is a' calling,
and the sky is clear and bright

84
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:32,821
misty mountains sing and beckon,
lead me out into the light

85
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:36,161
[ will ride, I will fly

86
00:07:36,206 --> 00:07:39,198
chase the wind and touch the sky

87
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:44,916
I will fly
chase the wind and touch the sky

88
00:07:50,053 --> 00:07:52,044
\whoo-hoo!

89
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:06,393
Where dark woods hide secrets
ahd mountains are fierce and bold

90
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:12,447
deep waters hold reflections
of times lost long ago

91
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:16,493
I will read every story,
take hold of my own dream

92
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,570
on!

93
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,740
Be as strong as the seas are stormy

94
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:24,580
and proud as an eagle's scream

95
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:27,587
[ will ride, I will fly

96
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:30,586
chase the wind and touch the sky

97
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:36,422
I will fly
chase the wind and touch the sky

98
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:48,941
And touch the sky

99
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:51,020
whoo!

100
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:54,280
Chase the wind

101
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:57,317
chase the wind

102
00:08:57,412 --> 00:09:02,577
touch the sky

103
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:14,339
I'm starving. You hungry too, Angus?

104
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,804
Pfft!

105
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,845
Oats it is, then.

106
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,721
Good day, Princess.

107
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:23,676
I cannot find the salt.
Where did you put it?

108
00:09:23,772 --> 00:09:26,172
It was over there a minute ago,
the last time I looked at it.

109
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:31,735
And then, out of nowhere,
the biggest bear you've ever seen!

110
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:34,984
His hide littered with the weapons
of fallen warriors.

111
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:38,651
His face scarred with one dead eye.

112
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,069
I drew my sword and...

113
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:42,700
Whoosh!

114
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,907
One swipe, his sword shattered.

115
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:48,118
Then chomp! Dad's leg was clean off.

116
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:50,871
Down the monster's throat it went.

117
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:53,877
Oh, that's my favorite part.

118
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:57,210
Mor'du has never been seen since,

119
00:09:57,347 --> 00:10:02,808
and is roaming the wilds
waiting his chance of revenge.

120
00:10:02,852 --> 00:10:05,343
Let him return.

121
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:07,520
I'll finish what I guddled
in the first place.

122
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:11,353
Merida, a Princess does not place
her weapons on the table.

123
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,652
Mum! It's just my bow.

124
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:17,689
A Princess should not have weapons
in my opinion.

125
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:19,073
Fergus: Leave her be.

126
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:22,031
Princess or not,
learning to fight is essential.

127
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:24,909
Mum?
You'll never guess what I did today.

128
00:10:24,999 --> 00:10:27,160
Hm?
I climbed the crone's tooth,

129
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,703
and drank from the fire falls.

130
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,664
Fire falls?

131
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:34,501
They say only the ancient kings
were brave enough to drink the fire.

132
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,422
What did you do, dear?
Nothing, mum.

133
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:39,969
Hungry, aren't we?

134
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:42,422
Mum!
You'll get dreadful collywobbles.

135
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:45,509
Oh, Fergus, will you look at
your daughter's plate?

136
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:47,553
So what?

137
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:50,096
Oh, you great...
Don't let them lick...

138
00:10:50,191 --> 00:10:51,522
Boys, you're naughty.

139
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:53,650
Don't just play with your haggis.

140
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:56,690
Urgh!
Och, how do you know you don't like it,

141
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,821
if you won't try it?

142
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,739
That's just a wee sheep's stomach.

143
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:03,443
It's delicious. Mm!

144
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:05,824
My lady.
Thank you, Maudie.

145
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:07,755
Fergus: You're getting too big,
the two of you.

146
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,081
Elinor: Aha.

147
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:15,539
From the lords macintosh,
macguffin and Dingwall.

148
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:16,957
Their responses, no doubt.

149
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,587
Aye, aye!

150
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:20,627
Fergus: Hey, hey!

151
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:24,176
Stay out of my food,
you greedy mongrels.

152
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:26,967
Chew on that, you manky dogs!

153
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:29,097
Fergus?

154
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:32,855
They've all accepted.

155
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:37,819
Who's accepted what, mother?

156
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:40,113
Boys, you are excused.

157
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:44,067
Oof!

158
00:11:44,746 --> 00:11:46,031
Hey!

159
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:49,831
What did I do now?

160
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:52,125
Your father has something
to discuss with you.

161
00:11:54,631 --> 00:11:55,791
Fergus?

162
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,498
Oh.

163
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,719
Er... Merida.

164
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:11,888
The lords are presenting
their sons as suitors for your betrothal.

165
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,814
What?
The clans have accepted.

166
00:12:15,485 --> 00:12:17,976
Dad!
What? I...

167
00:12:18,029 --> 00:12:20,190
You... she... Elinor?

168
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:22,863
Honestly, Merida, I don't know why
you're reacting this way.

169
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:27,986
This year, each clan will present a suitor
to compete in the games for your hand.

170
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:30,781
I suppose a Princess
just does what she's told?

171
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,245
A Princess does not raise her voice.

172
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:37,124
Merida, this is what you've been
preparing for your whole life.

173
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:41,087
No, it's what you've been preparing
me for my whole life.

174
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:43,509
I won't go through with it.
You can't make me.

175
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:45,712
Merida!

176
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:47,763
Huh? Merida!

177
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,520
Urgh!

178
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:53,845
Boys!

179
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:01,736
Mother. Suitors? Marriage?

180
00:13:01,823 --> 00:13:04,189
Once there was an ancient kingdom...

181
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,858
Oh, mum!

182
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:08,568
Ancient kingdom.

183
00:13:08,663 --> 00:13:10,699
Its name long forgotten,

184
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:15,284
ruled by a wise and fair king
who was much beloved.

185
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:20,789
And when he grew old he divided
the kingdom among his four sons,

186
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:25,252
that they should be the pillars
on which the peace of the land rested.

187
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:31,679
But the oldest prince
wanted to rule the land for himself.

188
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:35,312
He followed his own path
and the kingdom fell

189
00:13:36,607 --> 00:13:39,565
to war, and chaos and ruin.

190
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,563
That's a nice story.

191
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,895
It's not just a story, Merida.

192
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:47,073
Legends are lessons.
They ring with truths.

193
00:13:47,118 --> 00:13:48,574
Och, mum.

194
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,868
I would advise you
to make your peace with this.

195
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:52,744
The clans are coming
to present their suitors.

196
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:55,164
It's not fair.
Och, Merida.

197
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:57,993
It's marriage.
It's not the end of the world.

198
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:09,470
Fergus: You're muttering.
I don't mutter.

199
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:13,387
Aye, you do. You mutter, lass,
when something's troubling you.

200
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,726
I blame you. Stubbornness.

201
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:17,458
It's entirely from your side of the family.

202
00:14:17,482 --> 00:14:20,349
I take it the talk
didn't go too well, then?

203
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:22,934
Och, I don't know what to do.

204
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:26,066
Speak to her, dear.
I do speak to her.

205
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:29,403
She just doesn't listen.
Come on, now.

206
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:32,026
Pretend I'm Merida. Speak to me.

207
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:34,077
What would you say?

208
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,614
Och... I can't do this.

209
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,290
Sure you can.

210
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,960
There, there. That's my queen.

211
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:43,003
Right, here we go.

212
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:44,797
I don't want to get married.

213
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:47,341
I want to stay single
and let my hair flow in the wind

214
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:51,341
as I ride through the Glen
firing arrows into the sunset.

215
00:14:56,771 --> 00:15:01,765
Merida, all this work,
all the time spent preparing you,

216
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:05,436
schooling you,
giving you everything we never had.

217
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:09,154
I ask you, what do you expect us to do?

218
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:12,325
Call off the gathering.
Would that kill them?

219
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:13,743
You're the queen.

220
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:17,163
You can just tell the lords
the Princess is not ready for this.

221
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:20,871
In fact, she might not ever be ready
for this, so that's that.

222
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:25,001
Good day to you. We'll expect your
declarations of war in the morning.

223
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:28,800
I understand this must all seem unfair.

224
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:31,177
Even I had reservations
when I faced betrothal.

225
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:34,714
But we can't just run away
from who we are.

226
00:15:34,809 --> 00:15:37,300
I don't want my life to be over.

227
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,763
I want my freedom!

228
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:42,097
But are you willing to pay the price
your freedom will cost?

229
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:44,307
I'm not doing any of this to hurt you.

230
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:49,900
If you could just try to see what I do,
I do out of love.

231
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:52,949
But it's my life, it's...

232
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:55,109
I'm just not ready.

233
00:15:55,204 --> 00:15:57,069
I think you'd see, if you could just...

234
00:15:57,165 --> 00:16:00,202
I think I could make you understand
if you would just...

235
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:01,874
Listen.
__listen.

236
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,377
I swear, Angus,
this isn't going to happen.

237
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,000
Not if I have any say in it.

238
00:16:27,737 --> 00:16:29,318
Macguffin!

239
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:30,895
Men: Macguffin!

240
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,817
Dingwall!
Men: Dingwall!

241
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:40,450
Macintosh!
Men: Macintosh!

242
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,246
Ooh! Aah!

243
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:49,841
Oh.

244
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:56,929
You look absolutely beautiful.

245
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,301
I can't breathe.

246
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,383
Och, shush! Give us a turn.

247
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:04,140
I can't move.

248
00:17:04,232 --> 00:17:06,268
It's too tight.

249
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:09,101
It's perfect.

250
00:17:21,499 --> 00:17:24,036
Merida? Mum?

251
00:17:26,963 --> 00:17:28,954
Just...

252
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,833
Remember to smile.

253
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,311
Aye, they're coming.

254
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:51,688
Places, everyone. Places.

255
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:55,772
Ohl

256
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:11,170
I look fine, woman! Leave me be!

257
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:12,838
