01:04:48,802 --> 01:04:50,918
How do we know that
this isn't some trick?

786
01:04:50,970 --> 01:04:52,801
I'd never...
This is highly irregular.

787
01:04:52,889 --> 01:04:54,800
What are you playing at?
Where is the queen?

788
01:04:54,849 --> 01:04:57,495
Lord macintosh: We will not stand
for any more of this jiggery-pokery.

789
01:04:57,519 --> 01:04:59,680
That's right. Let's see her.
Shut it!

790
01:05:04,484 --> 01:05:06,645
Well, I, uh...

791
01:05:10,824 --> 01:05:11,824
Uh...

792
01:05:16,287 --> 01:05:19,905
Once there was an ancient kingdom.

793
01:05:20,166 --> 01:05:21,827
What is this?

794
01:05:21,876 --> 01:05:25,414
That kingdom fell into war

795
01:05:25,505 --> 01:05:27,587
and chaos and ruin...

796
01:05:27,674 --> 01:05:30,757
Och, we've all heard that tale.
Lost kingdom.

797
01:05:30,844 --> 01:05:32,425
Aye, but it's true.

798
01:05:32,512 --> 01:05:36,175
I know now how one selfish act
can turn the fate of a kingdom.

799
01:05:36,224 --> 01:05:37,660
Lord macguffin:
Bah, it's just a legend.

800
01:05:37,684 --> 01:05:39,424
Legends are lessons.

801
01:05:40,228 --> 01:05:42,310
They ring with truths.

802
01:05:43,356 --> 01:05:44,937
Our kingdom is young.

803
01:05:45,191 --> 01:05:47,307
Our stories are not yet legend.

804
01:05:47,360 --> 01:05:50,523
But in them, our bond was struck.

805
01:05:50,572 --> 01:05:52,688
Our clans were once enemies.

806
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:56,115
But when invaders threatened us
from the sea,

807
01:05:56,202 --> 01:05:59,194
you joined together to defend our lands.

808
01:05:59,747 --> 01:06:02,409
You fought for each other.

809
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:04,456
You risked everything for each other.

810
01:06:05,378 --> 01:06:07,790
Lord macguffin, my dad saved your life,

811
01:06:07,881 --> 01:06:10,418
stopping an arrow
as you ran to Dingwall's aid.

812
01:06:10,508 --> 01:06:12,339
Aye, and I'll never forget it.

813
01:06:12,385 --> 01:06:14,046
Merida: And, lord macintosh,

814
01:06:14,137 --> 01:06:17,470
you saved my dad
when you charged in on heavy horse

815
01:06:17,557 --> 01:06:19,263
and held off the advance.

816
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:23,389
And we all know how lord Dingwall
broke the enemy line.

817
01:06:23,480 --> 01:06:25,562
With a mighty throw of his spear!

818
01:06:25,607 --> 01:06:27,518
I was aiming at you, you big tumshie.

819
01:06:29,360 --> 01:06:32,727
The story of this kingdom
is a powerful one.

820
01:06:32,780 --> 01:06:35,362
My dad rallied your forces

821
01:06:35,408 --> 01:06:37,774
and you made him your king.

822
01:06:37,869 --> 01:06:41,953
It was an alliance forged in bravery
and friendship

823
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:43,780
and it lives to this day.

824
01:06:49,380 --> 01:06:51,837
But I've been selfish.

825
01:06:51,925 --> 01:06:54,962
I tore a great rift in our kingdom.

826
01:06:55,803 --> 01:06:57,885
There's no one to blame but me.

827
01:06:58,723 --> 01:07:02,432
And I know now
that I need to amend my mistake

828
01:07:03,603 --> 01:07:05,264
and mend our bond.

829
01:07:06,814 --> 01:07:10,648
And so, there is the matter
of my betrothal.

830
01:07:12,070 --> 01:07:15,403
I've decided to do what's right

831
01:07:15,448 --> 01:07:16,608
and...

832
01:07:17,450 --> 01:07:19,065
And...

833
01:07:19,786 --> 01:07:21,492
And...

834
01:07:22,497 --> 01:07:25,614
Break tradition.

835
01:07:32,006 --> 01:07:33,837
My mother...

836
01:07:35,134 --> 01:07:37,796
The queen, feels...

837
01:07:38,471 --> 01:07:41,634
Uh, in her heart

838
01:07:41,724 --> 01:07:43,635
that I...

839
01:07:45,353 --> 01:07:48,015
That we be free to...

840
01:07:49,399 --> 01:07:52,983
Write our own story...

841
01:07:54,737 --> 01:07:58,980
Follow our hearts

842
01:07:59,951 --> 01:08:03,569
and find love in our own time.

843
01:08:07,333 --> 01:08:10,416
That's beautiful.

844
01:08:10,503 --> 01:08:13,870
The queen and I put the decision
to you, my lords.

845
01:08:14,757 --> 01:08:18,670
Might our young people decide
for themselves who they will love?

846
01:08:18,720 --> 01:08:19,755
Huh?

847
01:08:19,846 --> 01:08:23,009
Well, since you've obviously
made up your minds about this,

848
01:08:23,057 --> 01:08:25,013
I have one thing to say.

849
01:08:25,101 --> 01:08:27,638
This is...
A grand ideal

850
01:08:27,687 --> 01:08:30,019
give us our own say
in choosing our fate.

851
01:08:30,064 --> 01:08:33,397
What?
Aye. Why shouldn't we choose?

852
01:08:33,526 --> 01:08:35,562
But she's the Princess.

853
01:08:35,653 --> 01:08:38,645
I did not pick her out. It was your idea.

854
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:41,940
And you... you feel the same way?

855
01:08:47,081 --> 01:08:49,538
Good?

856
01:08:52,170 --> 01:08:53,706
Well, that settles it.

857
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:58,540
Let these lads try and win her heart
before they win her hand.

858
01:08:58,593 --> 01:08:59,924
If they can.

859
01:09:00,011 --> 01:09:03,003
I say, the wee Dingwall
has a fighting chance.

860
01:09:03,056 --> 01:09:05,513
Fine, then. Seems for once we agree.

861
01:09:05,558 --> 01:09:08,595
It was my idea in the first place.

862
01:09:18,613 --> 01:09:20,524
Just like your mum.

863
01:09:20,573 --> 01:09:21,858
You devil.

864
01:09:27,538 --> 01:09:30,575
Uh... everyone to the cellar!

865
